      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Two crucial examples are *Griswold v. Connecticut*, which established a right to marital privacy, and *Roe v. Wade*, which recognized a constitutional right to an abortion based on personal autonomy. More recently, cases protecting aspects of personal liberty against government intrusion illustrate its ongoing use. Examining these cases shows how the Court has used due process to safeguard private spheres from state regulation.",
      "source": "target",
